01:17:01.746 --> 01:17:03.748
CASEY: [on mic]
Liam, this better work.

01:17:03.790 --> 01:17:06.292
LIAM: Here she comes.

01:17:06.334 --> 01:17:09.587
And here we go.

01:17:09.629 --> 01:17:13.675
[suspenseful music]

01:17:19.597 --> 01:17:20.724
CASEY: Rachel, how are you?

01:17:20.765 --> 01:17:21.891
-Honestly, I've been better.

01:17:21.933 --> 01:17:23.560
[laughs awkwardly]

01:17:23.601 --> 01:17:25.395
But talking design
about your gorgeous loft

01:17:25.437 --> 01:17:27.230
will help get the mind off it.

01:17:27.272 --> 01:17:28.356
Is it just us today?

01:17:28.398 --> 01:17:30.191
-It is!
Michael is stuck in a meeting.

01:17:30.233 --> 01:17:31.484
-Oh, that's too bad.

01:17:31.526 --> 01:17:34.571
-I'll fill him in on everything.

01:17:34.612 --> 01:17:35.947
Oh, what a lovely picture!

01:17:35.989 --> 01:17:38.074
Is that you as a kid?

01:17:38.116 --> 01:17:39.617
-Oh, yeah.

01:17:39.659 --> 01:17:41.411
I grew up sailing with my dad.

01:17:41.453 --> 01:17:43.455
Some of my best memories.

01:17:43.496 --> 01:17:46.291
-Is that what made you convince
your husband to get a boat?

01:17:46.332 --> 01:17:48.960
It must make you feel like
you're a kid again.

01:17:49.002 --> 01:17:51.046
Tell me, does he love it
as much as you do?

01:17:51.087 --> 01:17:52.380
LIAM: [on mic]
'Atta girl.

01:17:52.422 --> 01:17:54.424
-Well, now we know why
she's good with boat rope.

01:17:54.466 --> 01:17:56.217
-Um...

01:17:56.259 --> 01:17:57.594
I should...

01:17:57.635 --> 01:17:59.346
[emotionally] I...
Oh, I'm sorry.

01:17:59.387 --> 01:18:01.348
-Oh, Rachel!

01:18:01.389 --> 01:18:02.640
Oh, was it something I said?

01:18:02.682 --> 01:18:04.768
-No, it's not you.
It's, um...

01:18:04.809 --> 01:18:06.686
my husband...

01:18:06.728 --> 01:18:09.147
he, um...

01:18:09.189 --> 01:18:11.775
he died recently.

01:18:11.816 --> 01:18:14.611
-Oh, Rachel.
Oh, I am...

01:18:14.652 --> 01:18:16.279
so incredibly sorry.

01:18:16.321 --> 01:18:17.781
Ah.

01:18:17.822 --> 01:18:20.450
That's awful.
You must be so heartbroken.

01:18:20.492 --> 01:18:22.118
-I am. I...

01:18:22.160 --> 01:18:23.995
I don't know
how I'm gonna go on.

01:18:24.037 --> 01:18:27.248
I wanted to cancel today,
but I thought it might be good

01:18:27.290 --> 01:18:29.376
to just get my mind
off it for a bit.

01:18:29.417 --> 01:18:31.127
But I can't.

01:18:31.169 --> 01:18:33.463
I-I... I just can't
believe this is happening.

01:18:33.505 --> 01:18:35.882
I... I'm sorry.

01:18:35.924 --> 01:18:37.342
This is so unprofessional.

01:18:37.384 --> 01:18:39.678
-Oh, Rachel,
no, don't worry about it at all.

01:18:39.719 --> 01:18:42.097
You know, I know firsthand

01:18:42.138 --> 01:18:45.767
what it's like to lose
someone you love.

01:18:45.809 --> 01:18:47.060
Not my husband, of course.

01:18:47.102 --> 01:18:51.481
Michael's just fine, but...

01:18:51.523 --> 01:18:53.650
I recently lost my best friend.

01:18:53.692 --> 01:18:55.318
-Here we go.

01:18:55.360 --> 01:18:57.612
CASEY: She was...

01:18:57.654 --> 01:19:00.532
the sister I never had.

01:19:00.573 --> 01:19:04.411
Her name was Devina.

01:19:04.452 --> 01:19:06.996
I think you know her, right?

01:19:07.038 --> 01:19:11.334
Hm, that's what I thought.

01:19:11.376 --> 01:19:15.547
You know, Rachel, I gotta say,
I think that if I knew Michael

01:19:15.588 --> 01:19:19.592
was running around on me and...

01:19:19.634 --> 01:19:23.054
not valuing me and betraying me

01:19:23.096 --> 01:19:27.600
in the worst and most
humiliating way possible,

01:19:29.853 --> 01:19:34.566
I would probably want to kill
the person responsible as well.

01:19:38.069 --> 01:19:41.614
-She was threatening
to blow up our life.

01:19:41.656 --> 01:19:43.533
Do you know
how hard I've worked?

01:19:43.575 --> 01:19:47.787
Everything I've had to
put up with to have this?

01:19:47.829 --> 01:19:51.207
Kurt wouldn't do it,
so I had to!

01:19:51.249 --> 01:19:53.543
-[screams]

01:19:53.585 --> 01:19:55.503
-Go, go, go, go, go!

01:19:55.545 --> 01:19:57.380
Call the cops, call the cops!

01:19:57.422 --> 01:19:59.716
-Hey!
Hey, hey!

01:19:59.758 --> 01:20:01.885
-[Casey gasping]

01:20:01.926 --> 01:20:03.053
-Hey, are you okay?

01:20:03.094 --> 01:20:04.137
-Ow!

01:20:04.179 --> 01:20:05.513
LIAM: Eli, I need your help.

01:20:05.555 --> 01:20:06.723
-Yeah.

01:20:06.765 --> 01:20:07.766
RACHEL: Get off me!
Augh!

01:20:07.807 --> 01:20:09.768
LIAM: Hey, stop!

01:20:09.809 --> 01:20:11.144
[Rachel screams]

01:20:11.186 --> 01:20:13.146
-Casey!

01:20:13.188 --> 01:20:15.273
PJ: Police are on their way.

01:20:19.611 --> 01:20:21.071
You're okay!

01:20:28.203 --> 01:20:30.789
JUDGE: In our re-examining
of the evidence of innocence,

01:20:30.830 --> 01:20:32.499
which was not
presented at trial,

01:20:32.540 --> 01:20:35.752
the court relieves Marcus
Barlowe of all consequences

01:20:35.794 --> 01:20:39.756
of the criminal conviction
of murder in the second degree.

01:20:39.798 --> 01:20:43.051
-[gavel bangs]
-Court dismissed.

01:20:43.093 --> 01:20:47.764
[emotional, uplifting music]

