01:21:04.948 --> 01:21:06.408
CASEY: Well, they're
gonna process Marcus

01:21:06.449 --> 01:21:08.493
and get him out of here.
He's exonerated.

01:21:08.535 --> 01:21:11.121
He's finally free.

01:21:11.162 --> 01:21:13.456
I can't thank you enough
for everything you've done

01:21:13.498 --> 01:21:14.791
for my brother and me.

01:21:14.833 --> 01:21:16.668
I-I really can never repay you.

01:21:16.710 --> 01:21:18.795
-You don't owe us anything.

01:21:18.837 --> 01:21:20.630
PJ: I think we make
a pretty good team,

01:21:20.672 --> 01:21:22.007
us Justice Warriors!

01:21:22.048 --> 01:21:23.883
-[laughter]
-Not calling myself that.

01:21:23.925 --> 01:21:25.468
LIAM: You know,

01:21:25.510 --> 01:21:28.013
I actually have another case
I could use some help with.

01:21:28.054 --> 01:21:29.931
How's about I take you guys
to lunch and, uh,

01:21:29.973 --> 01:21:31.224
get your eyes on it?

01:21:31.266 --> 01:21:35.061
-Okay, it's a deal.
If you let me treat.

01:21:35.103 --> 01:21:36.896
-Sold.
-Alright.

01:21:36.938 --> 01:21:38.314
-She sold me.
-See ya.

01:21:38.356 --> 01:21:40.358
LIAM: You guys all heard that.
She's doin' it.

01:21:40.400 --> 01:21:42.277
PJ: I heard it.

01:21:42.318 --> 01:21:44.946
-I saw you talking
to DA Quinn earlier.

01:21:44.988 --> 01:21:46.531
Is everything okay?

01:21:46.573 --> 01:21:48.908
-Yeah, I mean, you know,
he's not real happy

01:21:48.950 --> 01:21:51.202
that I put myself in danger.
-Right.

01:21:51.244 --> 01:21:53.788
-But he's happy that justice
got served in the end.

01:21:53.830 --> 01:21:56.958
Rachel's all set for trial,
and between the tape of Kurt

01:21:57.000 --> 01:21:58.877
and the evidence we found,

01:21:58.918 --> 01:22:01.046
it's enough to prove
Frank's self-defence.

01:22:01.087 --> 01:22:03.423
-I'm glad to hear that.

01:22:03.465 --> 01:22:05.884
-And he offered me a full-time
position at the DA's office

01:22:05.925 --> 01:22:07.177
when I graduate.

01:22:07.218 --> 01:22:10.263
-What? Whoa, Casey!
That's amazing.

01:22:10.305 --> 01:22:11.848
-Thank you.
-Congratulations.

01:22:11.890 --> 01:22:14.225
-Thank you.
I turned him down.

01:22:14.267 --> 01:22:15.727
-Wha--

01:22:15.769 --> 01:22:17.645
-I asked to be transferred
to the conviction integrity unit

01:22:17.687 --> 01:22:20.732
next summer
for my last year's internship.

01:22:25.028 --> 01:22:26.529
Um...

01:22:26.571 --> 01:22:27.614
-Yeah?

01:22:27.655 --> 01:22:29.616
-I-I, um...

01:22:29.657 --> 01:22:32.744
I know we haven't
really had a chance to talk.

01:22:35.121 --> 01:22:38.875
I feel horrible
for the way that I behaved,

01:22:38.917 --> 01:22:42.545
and I owe you an explanation.

01:22:42.587 --> 01:22:45.090
-I'm listening.

01:22:45.131 --> 01:22:49.552
-I don't have
a Casey in my family.

01:22:49.594 --> 01:22:51.971
You know,
someone that'll stick up for you

01:22:52.013 --> 01:22:53.807
no matter what.

01:22:53.848 --> 01:22:56.601
Marcus is really lucky.

01:22:56.643 --> 01:23:00.772
And, if you'll let me...

01:23:00.814 --> 01:23:05.568
I'm gonna do my best to become
the man you believed in,

01:23:05.610 --> 01:23:08.905
and not the coward
that I have proven myself to be.

01:23:08.947 --> 01:23:11.658
-Hey, hey, hey.

01:23:11.700 --> 01:23:13.785
Don't talk about
my friend like that.

01:23:16.538 --> 01:23:19.082
-Am I the friend?
-Yes, you're the friend.

01:23:19.124 --> 01:23:22.127
-Okay.
Alright, come here.

01:23:22.168 --> 01:23:23.837
CASEY: Alright, y'all,
let's get outta here.

01:23:23.878 --> 01:23:25.338
SARAH: Oh, yeah.

01:23:25.380 --> 01:23:27.674
CASEY: So, are we actually
set on Justice Warriors?

01:23:27.716 --> 01:23:29.050
PJ: Yes, I'll make T-shirts!

01:23:29.092 --> 01:23:30.468
ELI: I'm not calling myself
a Justice Warrior.

01:23:30.510 --> 01:23:32.345
CASEY: Okay,
let's hold the roll.

01:23:32.387 --> 01:23:34.139
LIAM: It's grown on me,
I mean it.

